<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The position of the single genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1859" class="Hexapoda" family="Trogossitidae" genus="Calitys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<pageBreakToken pageId="8" pageNumber="9" start="start">Calitys</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the trogossitid system has changed many times over the past century or so. It has been classified within either 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Peltinae">Peltinae</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Trogossitinae">Trogossitinae</taxonomicName>
(compare, for example, 
<bibRefCitation author="Barron, JR" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" pagination="1 - 143" publicationUrl="10.4039/entm10375fv" refId="B13" refString="Barron, JR, 1971. A revision of the Trogositidae of America North of Mexico (Coleoptera: Cleroidea). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 75: 1 - 143, 10.4039/entm10375fv" title="A revision of the Trogositidae of America North of Mexico (Coleoptera: Cleroidea)." url="10.4039/entm10375fv" volume="75" year="1971">Barron 1971</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Crowson, RA" journalOrPublisher="Transaction of the Royal entomological Society of London" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" pagination="275 - 327" refId="B44" refString="Crowson, RA, 1964a. A review of the classification of Cleroidea (Coleoptera), with descriptions of two genera of Peltidae and of several new larval types. Transaction of the Royal entomological Society of London 116: 275 - 327" title="A review of the classification of Cleroidea (Coleoptera), with descriptions of two genera of Peltidae and of several new larval types." volume="116" year="1964 a">Crowson 1964a</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">vs</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Crowson, RA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal entomological Society of London (B)" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 20" refId="B48" refString="Crowson, RA, 1970. Further observations on Cleroidea (Coleoptera). Proceedings of the Royal entomological Society of London (B) 39: 1 - 20" title="Further observations on Cleroidea (Coleoptera)." volume="39" year="1970">Crowson 1970</bibRefCitation>
), then treated as a separate subfamily (
<bibRefCitation author="Crowson, RA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal entomological Society of London (B)" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 20" refId="B48" refString="Crowson, RA, 1970. Further observations on Cleroidea (Coleoptera). Proceedings of the Royal entomological Society of London (B) 39: 1 - 20" title="Further observations on Cleroidea (Coleoptera)." volume="39" year="1970">Crowson 1970</bibRefCitation>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Hexapoda" family="Trogossitidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trogossitidae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">s.str.</emphasis>
without 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Peltidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Peltidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ślipinski, SA" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="162" pageNumber="163" pagination="439 - 463" refId="B279" refString="Ślipinski, SA, 1992. Larinotinae - A new subfamily of Trogossitidae (Coleoptera), with notes on the constitution of Trogossitidae and related families of Cleroidea. Revue suisse de Zoologie 99: 439 - 463" title="Larinotinae - A new subfamily of Trogossitidae (Coleoptera), with notes on the constitution of Trogossitidae and related families of Cleroidea." volume="99" year="1992">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ślipiński">Ślipinski</normalizedToken>
1992
</bibRefCitation>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Hexapoda" family="Trogossitidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trogossitidae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">s.lat.</emphasis>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter, E" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen des naturforschenden Vereines in Bruenn" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" pagination="3 - 66" refId="B258" refString="Reitter, E, 1876. Systematische Eintheilung der Trogositidae. (Familia Coleopterorum). Verhandlungen des naturforschenden Vereines in Bruenn 14: 3 - 66" title="Systematische Eintheilung der Trogositidae. (Familia Coleopterorum)." volume="14" year="1876">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Reitter’s">Reitter's</normalizedToken>
early idea (1876)
</bibRefCitation>
that it might be classified within the former 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="tribe" tribe="Leperini">Leperini</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Leperinae">Leperinae</taxonomicName>
(i.e. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1854" lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="tribe" tribe="Gymnochilini">Gymnochilini</taxonomicName>
herein) is also interesting and worthy of review. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1859" class="Hexapoda" family="Trogossitidae" genus="Calitys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Calitys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs among the primitive fungivorous groups and has several features shared with 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Peltinae">Peltinae</taxonomicName>
, for example: robust mandibles with mola, flat body, wide pronotum, weakly asymmetrical antennal club, and absence of elytral interlocking mechanism. However, it also has bizarre sculptures on dorsal surface of body, wax scales, and tufts of rigid setae that together differentiate the genus from all other trogossitids. Its basal position in the trogossitine branch is based chiefly on procoxal cavities perfectly externally closed, presence of paragular sclerites in larval cranium and concave larval tergite IX. Wax scales and tufts of setae on head, antennae, elytra, and pronotum make it resemble 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1854" lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="tribe" tribe="Gymnochilini">Gymnochilini</taxonomicName>
. Nonetheless, it remains possible to imagine 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1859" class="Hexapoda" family="Trogossitidae" genus="Calitys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Calitys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also as a derived member of 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Peltinae">Peltinae</taxonomicName>
or even 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crowson" authorityYear="1964" lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lophocaterinae">Lophocaterinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
